of what we don't understand,</i>

222
00:37:25,176 --> 00:37:28,270
<i>I decide to reveal
as much as possible about myself,</i>

223
00:37:28,346 --> 00:37:30,678
<i>make a display.</i>

224
00:37:33,684 --> 00:37:35,515
<i>(wolf grunts)</i>

225
00:38:06,851 --> 00:38:09,752
<i>I haven't seen the wolf in two days.</i>

226
00:38:10,554 --> 00:38:16,424
<i>I know I was violating the distance
principle, moving so far into his territory.</i>

227
00:38:16,494 --> 00:38:20,988
<i>But since he hadn't seemed afraid of me,
I hoped that I could. . .</i>

228
00:38:21,065 --> 00:38:23,056
<i>(snuffling)</i>

229
00:38:30,608 --> 00:38:32,599
<i>(growling)</i>

230
00:38:42,653 --> 00:38:44,644
<i>(panting)</i>

231
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:28,355
<i>(urinating)</i>

232
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:38,171
<i>I didn't take it personally.</i>

233
00:39:38,242 --> 00:39:42,235
<i>This was a matter of principle,
a territorial dispute.</i>

234
00:39:42,313 --> 00:39:45,009
<i>And he had fired the first shot.</i>

235
00:39:45,082 --> 00:39:47,346
# What never?
No, never

236
00:39:47,852 --> 00:39:49,786
# What never?

237
00:39:49,854 --> 00:39:51,617
# Hardly ever

238
00:39:51,689 --> 00:39:54,783
# Hardly ever, ever sick at sea

239
00:39:54,859 --> 00:39:58,761
<i># So give five cheers and one cheer,,,</i>

240
00:40:01,699 --> 00:40:02,495
Oh!

241
00:40:02,566 --> 00:40:04,557
<i>(hums)</i>

242
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:11,375
# I am the very model
of a modern major general

243
00:40:11,442 --> 00:40:13,376
# I've information vegetable,
animal, and mineral

244
00:40:13,444 --> 00:40:15,435
# I know the kings of England
and I quote the fights historical

245
00:40:15,513 --> 00:40:18,846
# From Marathon to Waterloo
in order categorical

246
00:40:18,916 --> 00:40:21,441
# I'm very well acquainted too
with matters mathematical

247
00:40:21,519 --> 00:40:24,716
# I understand equations
both the simple and quadratical

248
00:40:24,789 --> 00:40:28,589
# About binomial theorem
I'm teeming with a lot of news

249
00:40:28,659 --> 00:40:33,426
# With many cheerful facts
about the square of the hypotenuse

250
00:40:33,497 --> 00:40:35,488
<i>(humming)</i>

251
00:40:43,374 --> 00:40:47,367
<i>27 cups of tea later, I completed
a two-acre circle around my tent,</i>

252
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:50,903
<i>including a 100-yard section
of the wolf's path.</i>

253
00:41:41,165 --> 00:41:44,601
<i>What had taken me six hours
and 27 cups of tea,</i>

254
00:41:44,668 --> 00:41:48,263
<i>he accomplished in just a few minutes.</i>

255
00:41:48,339 --> 00:41:52,435
<i>At each of the places that I'd marked,
he made his mark on the opposite side,</i>

256
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:56,378
<i>indicating that my boundary
was acceptable to him.</i>

257
00:42:03,354 --> 00:42:07,518
<i>And thus he granted me the space
for Lupus Base One.</i>

258
00:43:17,461 --> 00:43:20,328
<i>I'm supposed to watch his behavior,</i>

259
00:43:20,397 --> 00:43:25,334
<i>but all he does is stay
in front of his den and watch mine.</i>

260
00:43:25,402 --> 00:43:30,999
<i>I can't remember ever being the object
of so much constant attention.</i>

261
00:43:42,953 --> 00:43:45,285
<i>I now arise at 1 0: 00 in the evening,</i>

262
00:43:45,356 --> 00:43:50,419
<i>as everything becomes more active
during the long polar twilight.</i>

263
00:43:50,494 --> 00:43:53,952
<i>In my notebook,
the wolf has become George.</i>

264
00:44:15,686 --> 00:44:17,916
<i>The two are identical in color,</i>

265
00:44:17,988 --> 00:44:22,448
<i>with the same contrasting
shoulder marking and long-legged gait.</i>

266
00:44:22,526 --> 00:44:27,520
<i>But I've detected a difference,
and I've named her Angeline.</i>

267
00:44:46,250 --> 00:44:48,810
<i>As George has become a family of five,</i>

268
00:44:48,886 --> 00:44:54,188
<i>the reason for his long staring match
with me has lost its mystery.</i>

269
00:45:36,567 --> 00:45:41,004
<i>It's well-known that wolves mate for life,
but knowing that has hardly prepared me</i>

270
00:45:41,071 --> 00:45:45,007
<i>for their constant and varied
displays of affection.</i>

271
00:45:45,075 --> 00:45:48,806
<i>Every evening George goes off
on his nightly rounds.</i>

272
00:45:48,879 --> 00:45:52,940
<i>What he does on these excursions
remains a mystery to me.</i>

273
00:45:53,016 --> 00:45:55,746
<i>Angeline always remains
behind with the cubs,</i>

274
00:45:55,819 --> 00:45:59,311
<i>though I can see that she longs to follow.</i>

275
00:46:00,824 --> 00:46:02,815
<i>(howls)</i>

276
00:46:06,463 --> 00:46:08,454
<i>(distant howl)</i>

277
00:46:14,371 --> 00:46:16,862
<i>- (howls)
- (distant howl)</i>

278
00:46:23,113 --> 00:46:26,776
<i>(howling continues)</i>

279
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:02,118
<i>It's perplexing.</i>

280
00:47:02,186 --> 00:47:05,883
<i>The overall reason behind the study
is that the government wants final proof</i>

281
00:47:05,956 --> 00:47:11,588
<i>that wolves are responsible
for the disastrous decline in caribou.</i>

282
00:47:11,662 --> 00:47:19,000
<i>So far I haven 't seen a single caribou,
or observed the wolves eating anything.</i>

283
00:47:19,069 --> 00:47:21,697
<i>My own food supplies
are nearing exhaustion,</i>

284
00:47:21,772 --> 00:47:25,435
<i>and the local environment
offers scant pickings.</i>

285
00:47:25,509 --> 00:47:29,240
<i>Yet the wolves seem perfectly healthy.</i>

286
00:47:29,313 --> 00:47:31,474
<i>I've done numerous scatological studies</i>

287
00:47:31,548 --> 00:47:35,245
<i>and only turned up a smattering
of small mammal bones.</i>

288
00:47:35,319 --> 00:47:37,981
<i>The whole question of sustenance
around Lupus Base One</i>

289
00:47:38,055 --> 00:47:40,888
<i>has me completely mystified.</i>

290
00:47:47,998 --> 00:47:49,989
<i>(scratching)</i>

291
00:48:05,382 --> 00:48:07,373
<i>(squeals)</i>

292
00:48:13,357 --> 00:48:15,348
<i>(squeaks)</i>

293
00:48:17,327 --> 00:48:19,192
<i>(scuttling)</i>

294
00:48:47,457 --> 00:48:49,891
<i>Angeline has given me the first clue.</i>

295
00:48:49,960 --> 00:48:54,090
<i>In less than an hour
she's caught and consumed 23 mice.</i>

296
00:48:54,164 --> 00:48:57,656
<i>My rough calculation:
one mouse every ten square feet.</i>

297
00:48:57,734 --> 00:49:00,760
<i>Over 40,000 square feet in an acre.</i>

298
00:49:00,837 --> 00:49:03,931
<i>That's 4,000 mice per acre.</i>

299
00:49:12,816 --> 00:49:15,614
<i>The idea that a large animal
could live entirely on mice</i>

300
00:49:15,686 --> 00:49:18,382
<i>will be greeted with skepticism,</i>

301
00:49:18,455 --> 00:49:21,720
<i>unless I can perform an experiment.</i>

302
00:49:42,579 --> 00:49:44,240
<i>(squealing)</i>

303
00:49:44,314 --> 00:49:46,077
<i>(Tyler yells)</i>

304
00:49:46,783 --> 00:49:49,308
<i>(Tyler continues to yell)</i>

305
00:49:59,029 --> 00:50:01,156
<i>(yells)</i>

306
00:51:08,265 --> 00:51:10,256
<i>(crunching)</i>

307
00:52:11,328 --> 00:52:12,886
<i>(squeaks)</i>

308
00:52:20,270 --> 00:52:22,500
<i>(chuckles)</i>

309
00:52:22,572 --> 00:52:24,904
Arrr!

310
00:52:29,713 --> 00:52:31,704
<i>(growls)</i>

311
00:52:31,781 --> 00:52:33,681
<i>(squealing)</i>

312
00:53:26,270 --> 00:53:28,534
<i>(snarling)</i>

313
00:53:30,274 --> 00:53:33,607
<i>Five wolves appeared today.</i>

314
00:53:33,677 --> 00:53:37,841
<i>I expected one of the pack battles
I'd read so much about.</i>

315
00:53:37,914 --> 00:53:40,246
<i>It was Angie who was
right in the middle of things,</i>

316
00:53:40,317 --> 00:53:43,809
<i>asserting her position
as the dominant female.</i>

317
00:53:43,887 --> 00:53:46,481
<i>The challenges and assertions
were mostly symbolic.</i>

318
00:53:46,556 --> 00:53:48,547
<i>There was no real fighting.</i>

319
00:53:48,625 --> 00:53:51,389
<i>But Angeline got her point across.</i>

320
00:53:52,195 --> 00:53:54,026
<i>George was never challenged.</i>

321
00:53:54,097 --> 00:53:56,793
<i>He just stood there
with his air of masterful certainty,</i>

322
00:53:56,867 --> 00:53:59,495
<i>the alpha wolf of the pack.</i>

323
00:53:59,569 --> 00:54:02,367
<i>Usually, only the dominant pair
mate and have offspring,</i>

324
00:54:02,439 --> 00:54:05,499
<i>going to seek their own privacy
for that purpose.</i>

325
00:54:05,575 --> 00:54:09,807
<i>Apparently, the time had arrived
to rejoin the pack.</i>

326
00:54:38,175 --> 00:54:42,509
<i>There's a young brown wolf who seems
to be a particular favorite of the cubs.</i>

327
00:54:42,579 --> 00:54:45,173
<i>I've named him Uncle Albert.</i>

328
00:54:49,686 --> 00:54:54,817
<i>Now Angeline is free again
to join George on his nightly rounds.</i>

329
00:55:26,189 --> 00:55:28,180
<i>July 1 2.</i>

330
00:55:30,193 --> 00:55:35,062
<i>I wonder why it was that long ago
I became a watcher of things.</i>

331
00:55:35,132 --> 00:55:39,933
<i>Always watching others do and feel things
I wouldn't or couldn't do myself.</i>

332
00:55:41,705 --> 00:55:46,972
<i>Always standing off at a distance,
isolated, detached.</i>

333
00:55:48,879 --> 00:55:52,645
<i>I envy the wolves
for how they experience the world.</i>

334
00:55:52,716 --> 00:55:55,310
<i>Always in such direct contact
with their environment,</i>

335
00:55:55,385 --> 00:55:57,376
<i>traveling through their territories,</i>

336
00:55:57,454 --> 00:56:02,050
<i>alert and attuned to all the signs
coming in through their senses,</i>

337
00:56:02,125 --> 00:56:06,357
<i>telling them where a rabbit
recently passed or the sweet water lay,</i>

338
00:56:06,430 --> 00:56:10,958
<i>revealing a whole universe to them
that we can never really know.</i>

339
00:56:15,005 --> 00:56:20,705
<i>But I sit behind glass lenses,
filling up notebooks and triplicate forms,</i>

340
00:56:20,777 --> 00:56:26,079
<i>trying to capture the wolves
within the pages of my journal.</i>

341
00:56:26,149 --> 00:56:29,744
<i>And what'll be done with the study
when I'm finished?</i>

342
00:56:29,820 --> 00:56:33,620
<i>Once these wolves
have been exposed to my world. . .</i>

343
00:56:34,357 --> 00:56:37,190
<i>what will happen to them ?</i>

344
00:56:56,546 --> 00:57:00,573
<i>There's a strange wolf
that I only see fleetingly.</i>

345
00:57:02,152 --> 00:57:06,248
<i>He must be part of the pack,
but an outsider,</i>

346
00:57:06,323 --> 00:57:08,985
<i>always following at a distance.</i>

347
00:57:10,427 --> 00:57:13,089
<i>Perhaps another watcher.</i>

348
00:58:25,602 --> 00:58:28,230
<i>(high-pitched bird call)</i>

349
00:58:28,305 --> 00:58:30,296
Oh!

350
00:59:00,737 --> 00:59:03,706
<i>Ootek thought you might need
some company,</i>

351
00:59:05,041 --> 00:59:06,633
Ootek?

352
00:59:11,014 --> 00:59:13,005
<i>Hello,</i>

353
00:59:27,731 --> 00:59:30,427
<i>Really can't tell you how glad I am
to see the two of you,</i>

354
00:59:30,500 --> 00:59:34,163
<i>It's been so long
since I heard another human voice,</i>

355
00:59:34,771 --> 00:59:37,103
You have any ketchup here?

356
00:59:37,841 --> 00:59:41,777
<i>No, I don't, I'm sorry,
I ran out a couple of weeks ago,</i>

357
00:59:41,845 --> 00:59:44,336
<i>Here, have some fish,</i>

358
00:59:46,683 --> 00:59:48,548
<i>Uh, no,</i>

359
00:59:48,618 --> 00:59:51,109
<i>No, thanks, I don't eat fish,</i>

360
00:59:53,923 --> 00:59:56,255
What do you eat?

361
00:59:56,726 --> 00:59:58,717
<i>Actually,,,</i>

362
00:59:59,896 --> 01:00:02,057
<i>I eat mice,</i>

363
01:00:04,234 --> 01:00:07,533
<i>- You eat mice?
- Yeah,</i>

364
01:00:12,008 --> 01:00:14,499
<i>(speaks native language)</i>

365
01:00:16,913 --> 01:00:19,711
<i>It's an experiment, really,</i>

366
01:00:19,783 --> 01:00:23,549
<i>You see, the wolves are supposed to eat
caribou, However, there are no caribou,</i>

367
01:00:23,620 --> 01:00:26,145
<i>Basically, what the wolves
have been eating is mice,</i>

368
01:00:26,222 --> 01:00:30,921
So I'm conducting an experiment
to see whether a carnivore, a big animal,

369
01:00:30,994 --> 01:00:33,053
<i>can live on nothing but mice,</i>

370
01:00:33,129 --> 01:00:37,566
<i>So I've been just eating mice,
and I'm doing fine,</i>

371
01:00:41,337 --> 01:00:43,328
<i>(translates)</i>

372
01:01:01,558 --> 01:01:05,722
<i>- What does he say?
- He says, "Good idea,"</i>

373
01:01:09,933 --> 01:01:12,595
<i>(two men speak native language)</i>

374
01:01:16,439 --> 01:01:18,634
<i>(Tyler) Syringe,</i>

375
01:01:18,708 --> 01:01:20,699
<i>There,</i>

376
01:01:28,384 --> 01:01:32,844
<i>- What's that?
- Clamp, This thing? Yeah,</i>

377
01:01:32,922 --> 01:01:34,981
See the way this is set up here?

378
01:01:35,058 --> 01:01:38,653
<i>This is so it grabs ahold, You got him,</i>

379
01:01:38,728 --> 01:01:40,719
<i>(speaks native language)</i>

380
01:01:41,898 --> 01:01:44,128
<i>It's a gripper,</i>

381
01:01:44,200 --> 01:01:46,430
<i>(speaks native language)</i>

382
01:01:46,503 --> 01:01:49,097
<i>I know what that is,
They had them at the mines,</i>

383
01:01:49,172 --> 01:01:53,700
<i>Yeah, that's right, It's a gas mask,
except that I use it for wolf scats,</i>

384
01:01:53,777 --> 01:01:59,181
<i>The wolf scat has little tiny animals,
little tiny parasites,</i>

385
01:01:59,249 --> 01:02:02,776
And if you breathe these things in,
you breathe these little guys,

386
01:02:02,852 --> 01:02:07,448
<i>they go up into your brain
and they eat it out,</i>

387
01:02:07,524 --> 01:02:09,890
Scat? What is scat?

388
01:02:10,326 --> 01:02:11,918
<i>Uh,,,</i>

389
01:02:11,995 --> 01:02:14,054
<i>Wolf droppings,</i>

390
01:02:14,130 --> 01:02:18,328
See, the idea behind this is
if you study what comes out of a wolf,

391
01:02:18,401 --> 01:02:21,768
<i>you get a pretty good idea what went in,</i>

392
01:02:21,838 --> 01:02:23,669
<i>Hmm,</i>

393
01:02:23,740 --> 01:02:27,801
<i>I got a whole bag of them down there,
I got a whole sack,</i>

394
01:02:27,877 --> 01:02:29,868
<i>(translates)</i>

395
01:02:37,787 --> 01:02:40,119
<i>(speaks native language)</i>

396
01:02:43,960 --> 01:02:45,951
What did he say?

397
01:02:46,029 --> 01:02:48,759
<i>He says, "Good idea,"</i>

398
01:03:08,985 --> 01:03:10,976
<i>(howling)</i>

399
01:03:19,529 --> 01:03:21,520
<i>(howling continues)</i>

400
01:03:28,705 --> 01:03:31,037
<i>(speak native language)</i>

401
01:03:42,785 --> 01:03:46,653
<i>And so they settled in with me,
as if nothing could be more natural.</i>

402
01:03:51,027 --> 01:03:54,463
<i>For my part,
I'm glad to have the company.</i>

403
01:03:54,530 --> 01:03:56,521
<i>A seven,</i>

404
01:04:00,436 --> 01:04:02,427
<i>Mike had gone to school in the south.</i>

405
01:04:02,505 --> 01:04:04,905
<i>When his parents died,
Ootek adopted him.</i>

406
01:04:04,974 --> 01:04:08,933
<i>Traditionally, they are no orphans
among the Inuit.</i>

407
01:04:09,012 --> 01:04:11,503
<i>(plays stilted tune)</i>

408
01:04:22,659 --> 01:04:25,856
I met a girl in a bar,

409
01:04:25,929 --> 01:04:29,057
<i>and she wanted me to buy her drinks,
so I bought her some,</i>

410
01:04:29,132 --> 01:04:33,466
<i>And then after a while,
she wanted to come home with me,</i>

411
01:04:33,536 --> 01:04:37,632
<i>But I made a mistake,</i>

412
01:04:37,707 --> 01:04:40,369
<i>I smiled at her,</i>

413
01:04:41,144 --> 01:04:45,740
<i>That's what happens when a meat eater
becomes a sugar eater,</i>

414
01:05:00,263 --> 01:05:03,460
<i>Ootek has taken
a particular interest in the study,</i>

415
01:05:03,533 --> 01:05:09,961
<i>though I've learned there is little about
wolves that he doesn 't already know.</i>

416
01:05:16,479 --> 01:05:19,243
<i>But I sense there is another side to Ootek,</i>

417
01:05:19,315 --> 01:05:22,250
<i>some part of his nature
that he hasn 't shown.</i>

418
01:05:22,318 --> 01:05:24,479
<i>I try not to annoy him
with too many questions,</i>

419
01:05:24,554 --> 01:05:27,921
<i>but there are many things I'd like to know.</i>

420
01:05:54,117 --> 01:05:56,449
<i>(speaks native language)</i>

421
01:06:01,924 --> 01:06:05,690
<i>When he was young
he used to follow the wolves on their hunts,</i>

422
01:06:07,096 --> 01:06:09,428
<i>(speaks native language)</i>

423
01:06:12,368 --> 01:06:16,065
<i>The wolf is his helping spirit: amarok.</i>

424
01:06:18,908 --> 01:06:21,741
<i>- Ama...
- Amarok.</i>

425
01:06:21,811 --> 01:06:23,802
<i>- Ama...
- The wolf,</i>

426
01:06:23,880 --> 01:06:26,371
<i>(speaks native language)</i>

427
01:06:37,193 --> 01:06:42,495
<i>He went 30 days without food
and without protection from the cold,</i>

428
01:06:49,705 --> 01:06:52,196
<i>Then he saw the wolf,</i>

429
01:06:59,749 --> 01:07:03,742
<i>He felt the wolf bite into his heart,</i>

430
01:07:10,326 --> 01:07:15,127
<i>When he woke up, he was all in one piece,</i>

431
01:07:17,033 --> 01:07:21,436
<i>That's how the wolf
became his helping spirit,</i>

432
01:07:33,850 --> 01:07:35,841
<i>(howling)</i>

433
01:08:25,635 --> 01:08:28,866
<i>I wonder what makes them howl like that,</i>

434
01:08:31,340 --> 01:08:34,332
<i>They howl when they're lonely,</i>

435
01:08:36,812 --> 01:08:39,303
<i>Or to call their friends,</i>

436
01:08:41,384 --> 01:08:45,878
<i>That way, the other,,,
the others will know where they are,</i>

437
01:08:45,955 --> 01:08:49,891
<i>and then sooner or later
they're bound to meet up,</i>

438
01:08:53,095 --> 01:08:57,259
<i>That's the way to catch wolves,
Go where they're howling,</i>

439
01:08:57,333 --> 01:09:00,302
Hide behind a rock,

440
01:09:00,369 --> 01:09:02,735
<i>and then howl like one of them,</i>

441
01:09:02,805 --> 01:09:07,242
<i>And then,,, they will come to investigate,</i>

